	</head>
    <body>
        <div class="container">
			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-md-12">
					<div class="page-header">
						<h1 id="header" class="text-center">ACWPD Random Password Generator</h1>
					</div>
					<p>
						This tool will generate a password for you using <a href="https://www.random.org/">Random.Org's</a> true random numbers. While the password is not guarenteed to be unique, there is a high probability that it is. It's also not something that can be guessed, as it's random.
					</p>
					<p>
						These passwords are not designed to be memorized; they're designed for use with password managers, such as those built in to modern browsers, or standalone products. Because of this, they have a lot of characters in them, many of which are "special". We're working on a way to ensure that each password includes 1 capital, 1 lower-case, 1 number, and 1 special character; until we have that feature in place, please just generate a new password if the one(s) you generated didn't meet your requirements.
					</p>
					<p>
						We've written an <a href="/discussion-of-passwords">article</a> explining why this site is needed. <a href="/discussion-of-passwords">Give it a read</a> if you want.
					</p>
					<p>
						<a href="http://www.xkcd.com">The webcomic XKCD</a> has (as is so often the case) a comic that is relevant: <a href="https://xkcd.com/936/">Check it out! (And then come back)</a>. Because of the popularity of this method, we offer a "passphrase" option, which will generate this style of password. "Standard" is the traditional numbers/letters/symbols kind.
					</p>
				</div>
				<div class="col-md-12">
					<a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg btn-block toggle" href="#" role="button" id="switchToPhrase">Switch to Passphrase style</a>
					<a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg btn-block toggle hidden" href="#" role="button" id="switchToStandard">Switch to Standard style</a>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-md-4 toggle" id="standard">
					<form role="form"class="standards">
						<div class="form-group">
							<label for="password-length ">
								Number of characters in password
							</label>
							<input type="number" class="form-control" name="password-length" id="password-length" value="15" />
						</div>
						<div class="form-group">
							<label for="password-count">
								Number of passwords to generate
							</label>
							<input type="number" class="form-control" name="password-count" id="password-count" value="2" />
						</div>
						<div class="form-group">
							<label for="character-range">
								Type the characters you want to exclude
							</label>
							<input type="text" class="form-control" name="exclude" id="exclude" value="1i|Il!0oO`'.,_-;:" />
						</div>
						<a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg btn-block" ic-post-to="/a/password" ic-target="#passwords">
							Get passwords!
						</a>
					</form>
				</div>
				<div class="col-md-4 toggle hidden" id="phrase">
					<form role="form" class="phrases">
						<div class="form-group">
							<label for="password-length ">
								Number of words in passphrase
							</label>
							<input type="number" class="form-control" name="password-length" id="password-length" value="4" />
						</div>
						<div class="form-group">
							<label for="password-count">
								Number of passwords to generate
							</label>
							<input type="number" class="form-control" name="password-count" id="password-count" value="2" />
						</div>
						<a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg btn-block" ic-post-to="/a/passphrase" ic-target="#passwords">
							Get passwords!
						</a>
					</form>
				</div>
				<div class="col-md-4 toggle" id="standard-desc">
					<p>
						Your password will include only characters from this list:
					</p>
					<ul class="list-inline" id="all-characters">
						
					</ul>
					
				</div>
				<div class="col-md-4 toggle hidden" id="phrase-desc">
					<p>
						Your passphrase will consist of several words (your choice how many) selected from <a href="http://www.wordnik.com/">Wordnik</a>'s Dictionaries. For consistancy, all words are lower-case, regardless of original usage (even words that are only proper nouns, such as 'Doug', 'Portugal', or 'San Antonio'). Additionally, if there is a space in the word ('Los Angeles' or 'ice cream'), that space is replaced with an underscore (_). These phrases are almost certain to NOT include numbers or special characters.
					</p>
					<ul class="list-inline" id="all-characters">
						
					</ul>
					
				</div>
				<div class="col-md-4" id="passwords">
					
				</div>
			</div>

		</div>
		<div class="hidden" id="scripts">
			<script	src="/js/jquery-3.2.1.min.js"></script>
			<script src="/js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>
			<script	src="/js/intercooler-1.1.2.min.js"></script>
			<script src="/js/characters.js"></script>
			<script language="javascript">
				let phraseBtn = document.querySelector('#switchToPhrase');
					phraseBtn.addEventListener('click', function () {
						let toggle = document.querySelectorAll('.toggle');
						toggle.forEach(el => el.classList.toggle('hidden'));
					});
				let standardBtn = document.querySelector('#switchToStandard');
					standardBtn.addEventListener('click', function () {
						let toggle = document.querySelectorAll('.toggle');
						toggle.forEach(el => el.classList.toggle('hidden'));
					});

			</script>
		</div>
    </body>
</html>
